              <table id="EditorialReviewsPanel" class="ReviewSection" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%"><tr><td>
	
                <DIV class="ReviewHeading">Book Description:</DIV>
                <span id="Label1"> Here's a fast way for any programmer to begin writing professional Microsoft Windows-based applications for the Microsoft .NET platform-and extend them to the Web-one step at a time. Best-selling author Michael Halvorson shows how to unleash the power of the new version of Visual Basic, with coverage of programming fundamentals, Windows Forms, debugging, error handling, application deployment, object-oriented design, printing, and database access. The book also includes an introduction to creating Web applications, information on upgrading your Visual Basic 6 applications to Visual Basic .NET, and practice files on CD-ROM. </span>
              
</td></tr></table>
